<h2 id="doing-business-with-companies-house">Doing business with Companies House</h2>

<p>We use 2 systems to advertise and manage our contracts:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
<a href="https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder">Contracts Finder</a>, a free service for businesses, government buyers and the public</li>
  <li>
<a rel="external" href="http://ted.europa.eu/TED/main/HomePage.do">Tenders Electronic Daily (TED)</a>, which provides adverts and notices for tenders and contracts subject to EU procurement thresholds</li>
</ul>

<p>For simple low value purchases we use a quotation procedure, and award business via an official purchase order, or by government procurement card if the order value is under Â£1,000.</p>

<p>For higher value or more complex work we use a formal tendering process. We evaluate tenders by determining the most economically advantageous offer considering such factors as cost, quality, delivery and environmental impact.</p>

<h2 id="contact-us">Contact us</h2>

<p>You can contact us about procurement at:</p>

<div class="contact">
<p><strong>Companies House</strong>
<a href="mailto:enquiries@companieshouse.gov.uk">enquiries@companieshouse.gov.uk</a><br></br>
Telephone: 0303 1234 500<br></br>
Monday to Friday, 8.30am to 6pm<br></br>
<a href="https://www.gov.uk/call-charges">Find out about call charges</a></p>
